    "texture": {
      "default": "pad_bed",
      "rules": [
        { "when": [ {"knob":"subject_energy","op":"ge","lo":0.45,"hi":0.0},
                    {"knob":"fg_bg_contrast","op":"ge","lo":0.25,"hi":0.0} ],
          "pick": "pad_figured" },
        { "_comment": "S45/Slice-1 RE-TUNE: gate the CounterMelody routing on fg_bg_contrast, NOT foreground_energy. A feature-distribution probe over all 6 test images showed foreground_energy is a near-dead axis (real images emit 0.003-0.039, tightly clustered 4-10x BELOW the old 0.15 floor) so the counter routing fired on ZERO real images. fg_bg_contrast is the well-separated discriminating knob (0.052-0.341 across the set). The fe>=0.015 term is therefore only a TOKEN FLOOR (every real image clears it); fg_bg_contrast>=0.15 is the REAL gate. This routes the three structured images (AudioHaxImg1 ct=0.341, AudioHaxImg2 ct=0.284, AudioHaxImg3 ct=0.203) to the moving CounterMelody and keeps the two calmest (Lena ct=0.052, magicstudio ct=0.084) on the static pad_bed fallback. example.jpg (ct=0.136, below this gate but colorful) stays on pad_broken_wave. AudioHaxImg3 (colorfulness 0.423 would otherwise select pad_broken_wave) is INTENTIONALLY routed to the counter here: it sits AHEAD of pad_broken_wave in the table, so a structured colorful image gets the moving contrapuntal line rather than the broken-wave figuration — a deliberate musical call (structured subject -> moving counter), left for the operator to ear-judge. Both thresholds are operator-tunable.",
